text: Bash-Shidy () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Bashshidinsky Selsoviet, Nurimanovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 228 as of 2010. There are 4 streets. == Geography == It is located 7 km from Krasnaya Gorka. == References == Category:Rural localities in Nurimanovsky District
title: Bash-Shidy
